    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="75"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Calvo</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 1st instant, with which you inclose copy of the convention
                    between Costa Rica and Nicaragua for the demarcation of the boundary between the
                    two countries, one of the articles of which provides for the appointment by the
                    President of the United States of an engineer to decide any point of
                    disagreement between their respective commissioners.</p>
                <p>The President will be happy to appoint an engineer in accordance with the
                    above-referred-to provision upon the receipt of the joint request of the two
                    Governments.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
